Project Specification: ShelfSage (24h Hackathon Version)

Tagline: “Never waste a bite. Smart pantry management for home users and small businesses.”

1. Scope
Target: homeowners, students, families
Core goal: let users log items, track expiration, and get daily usage suggestions
Build a working, visual demo in 24h
Skip advanced features like full meal plans, push notifications, or voice in MVP
2. Core Features (MVP)
Item Logging
Upload photo or manual entry (skip barcode scanning if too slow)
Input: name, quantity, expiration date, optional category
AI Usage Suggestions
Simple template-based prompts:
“Use [item] today in [common use]”
Pre-generate suggestions for demo items to save time
Dashboard
Display items in list + simple color coding:
Red = use today
Yellow = soon
Green = safe
Optional small “weekly waste saved” stat
Demo Items
Pre-populate 10–15 common pantry items (milk, eggs, bread, cheese, veggies)
3. Technical Stack
Frontend: React or simple HTML/CSS/JS
Upload/manual entry form
Dashboard with list + color-coded items
Backend: Node.js or Python Flask/FastAPI
Endpoints:
POST /add-item → log item
GET /dashboard → fetch all items + suggestions
Database: MongoDB Atlas free tier
Collections: users, items, suggestions
AI: Gemini or open-source LLM
Generate simple usage suggestions from item name + expiration
Pre-fill suggestions for demo items for speed
4. MVP Flow (~2 min demo)
Open dashboard → empty
Upload 3–5 items (milk, eggs, bread) → items appear with red/yellow/green highlight
Click an item → shows AI usage suggestion
Dashboard shows summary: “3 items expiring soon”
5. Hackathon Shortcuts
Pre-populate 10–15 items + AI suggestions to make the demo instant
Skip complex barcode scanning → use manual entry or sample photos
Keep dashboard simple (list + color highlights)
6. Optional Enhancements (if time permits)
Pantry layout visualization
Quick “combine items into a simple recipe” AI suggestion
Add one or two voice tips using ElevenLabs (short, pre-recorded)
7. GitHub Deployment
Push all code + demo data to: https://github.com/ivyyy23/ShelfSage.git
Suggested structure:
/frontend
/backend
/database
/demo-data